    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/1877a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="93" xml:id="d1113fn93">Same to Consul Canada at Vera Cruz with
                        instruction to, repeat to Consul at Tampico.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As the reasons which influenced this Government heretofore to furnish assistance
                    and transportation to American citizens in Mexico <pb facs="0806" n="690"
                        xml:id="pg_690"/> appear to exist no longer, you are instructed to decline
                    hereafter all such applications. So inform all Consuls in your district.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
